OL,6,FFor twenty years after Biddy Baxter's
OL,7,Fdeparture in 1988, subsequent editors
OL,8,Fdid an amazing job ` respecting the
OL,9,Fprogramme's past and traditions while
OL,10,Falso modernising the style and content.
OL,12,FSince the late-noughties the format,
OL,13,Fcontent and style of presentation have
OL,14,Fbeen very different. That is not said
OL,15,Fas a criticism. The programme exists
OL,16,Ffor today's children ` not its former
OL,17,Fviewers.
OL,19,FBut it remains a programme which is
OL,20,Floved by many who have not seen it for
OL,21,Fa long time.
